{"author":"Iso Tester","data":{"body":"SCOPE DECISION (this session) — completing the epic's remaining workstreams.\n\nRe-triage (confirmed against code this session): WS-INTENT-ALIGN, WS-MIGRATE, WS-PROMPTS, WS-CLEANUP, WS-VISUAL, WS-VALIDATE are all DONE via the closed sibling epics A (sage-votary-logic/5766) + B (peak-fir-hilt/72d5) and e6d9. Genuinely remaining: WS-DOC, WS-EVAL-EXISTING, WS-VISUAL-EVAL.\n\nDECISIONS:\n1. WS-EVAL-EXISTING = FULL build (Phase 1 + Phase 2). Phase 1: author the 3 missing eval specs (completion-verifier, ticket-quality, spec-alignment) + offline discipline unit tests. Phase 2: make evals actually RUN — the live tier is currently an unwired stub (run_eval() raises NotImplementedError; deterministic scorer names are inert strings with NO registry/dispatch; eval-live promptfoo step is a placeholder echo). Phase 2 sub-deliverables: 2.1 deterministic-scorer registry + ~12 impls; 2.2 live solver w/ context-injection + repo-tool stubbing (the 3 reviewers are store+repo-coupled agentic ops, not inline-feedable); 2.3 per-reviewer dataset schema + validation (incl scan_spec BATCH unit); 2.4 fixture corpus + label adjudication (completion-verifier needs source-citation fixtures); 2.5 Inspect Task glue + eval-live CI wiring (workflow_dispatch + weekly schedule, non-blocking, cached, concurrency-capped, dashboard spend cap). Design aligns with 2025-26 community consensus (two-tier: deterministic gate every PR; LLM-judge off-PR-path, non-blocking). Benefits ALL 7 specs.\n2. WS-VISUAL-EVAL = SPLIT OFF into its own epic (out of scope for 6f2d). The epic frames it as a decision WS; carving it out so 6f2d can close on DOC+EVAL.\n\nEval plan was adversarially reviewed by subagent (community-standards/maintainability/reliability/correctness/fitness); the inert-scorer-registry + agentic-reviewer-not-inline-feedable findings are folded into Phase 2 above."},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"COMMENT","timestamp":1782578428539872001,"uuid":"c547356b-1bdb-4747-a3a6-50fbf8a56b01"}